const Q_IRK_2017_MODEL=[{"id": "objective>IRK>2017 Model>1", "question": "<div style=\"font-family:Cambria;font-size:17px;\">Every human being, according to Sūrah al- Asr is in a state of loss, except the  <br/> </div>", "options": ["<div style=\"font-family:Cambria;font-size:17px;\">Quraish tribe </div>", "<div style=\"font-family:Cambria;font-size:17px;\">the oppressed people </div>", "<div style=\"font-family:Cambria;font-size:17px;\">faithful and righteous </div>", "<div style=\"font-family:Cambria;font-size:17px;\">earlier generations  <br/> </div>"], "answer": 2, "explanation": "<div style=\"font-family:Cambria;font-size:17px;\">save those who have faith and do righteous deeds, and counsel each other to hold on to truth and counsel each other to be steadfast. This Surah an oath has been sworn by the Time to impress the point that man is in sheer loss and only those people are an exception from the loss who are characterized by four qualities: <br/> (1) Faith. <br/> (2) Righteous deeds. <br/> (3) Exhorting one another to truth. <br/> (4) Exhorting one another to patience <br/> </div>", "topic": "ARTICLE OF FAITH : THE LAST DAY: YAWM-AL-BA'TH"}, {"id": "objective>IRK>2017 Model>2", "question": "<div style=\"font-family:Cambria;font-size:17px;\"> <img src=\"data:image/png;base64,\" style=\"position:relative;max-width:100%;\"/> <br/> The translation of the verse above is  </div>", "options": ["<div style=\"font-family:Cambria;font-size:17px;\">'truly, man is to his lord ungrateful </div>", "<div style=\"font-family:Cambria;font-size:17px;\"> 'verily, to thy Lord is the return of all</div>", "<div style=\"font-family:Cambria;font-size:17px;\">'And verily the hereafter will be better for thee than present </div>", "<div style=\"font-family:Cambria;font-size:17px;\">'truly, he succeeds that purifies </div>"], "answer": 1, "explanation": "<div style=\"font-family:Cambria;font-size:17px;\">Surah Al-Alaq (96:8) 'Verily, to the Lord is the return of all' .  <br/>  That is, whatever he might have attained in the world, which makes him behave arrogantly and rebelliously, in the end he has to return to your Lord. Then he will realize what fate awaits him in consequence of his such attitude and behavior. <br/> </div>", "topic": "ARTICLE OF FAITH : BELIEF IN ALLAH"}, {"id": "objective>IRK>2017 Model>3", "question": "<div style=\"font-family:Cambria;font-size:17px;\">The verse that can be recited for protection against evil machinations is  <br/> </div>", "options": ["<div style=\"font-family:Cambria;font-size:17px;\">Q. 2:286 </div>", "<div style=\"font-family:Cambria;font-size:17px;\">Q. 2:285 </div>", "<div style=\"font-family:Cambria;font-size:17px;\">Q. 2:256 </div>", "<div style=\"font-family:Cambria;font-size:17px;\">Q. 2:255 </div>"], "answer": 3, "explanation": "<div style=\"font-family:Cambria;font-size:17px;\">Allah, the Ever-Living, the Self-Subsisting by Whom all subsist, there is no god but He.  Neither slumber seizes Him, nor sleep; to Him belongs all that is in the heavens and all that is in the earth. Who is there who might intercede with Him save with His leave?  <br/> He knows what lies before them and what is hidden from them, whereas they cannot attain to anything of His knowledge save what He wills them to attain. His Dominion  overspreads the heavens and the earth, and their upholding wearies Him not. He is All-High, All-Glorious. Irrespective of the number of gods or objects of worship set up by ignorant people, the fact remains that godhead in its entirety, belongs exclusively to the Eternal Being, Who is indebted to no one for His existence. In fact, He is not only self-existent, but upon Him rests the entire order of the universe. He alone wields all sovereign authority over His dominion. None shares either His attributes or His power and might, and no one has the same claims against the creatures as He. Hence, if anywhere in the heavens or the earth someone sets up anything or anybody as an object of worship and service (ilah) either instead of or in addition to the One True God this amounts to declaring war on reality. <br/> </div>", "topic": "ARTICLE OF FAITH : BELIEF IN ALLAH"}, {"id": "objective>IRK>2017 Model>4", "question": "<div style=\"font-family:Cambria;font-size:17px;\">The official compilation of Hadith was facilitated by  <br/> </div>", "options": ["<div style=\"font-family:Cambria;font-size:17px;\">Caliph Umar b. al-khattab </div>", "<div style=\"font-family:Cambria;font-size:17px;\">Caliph Uthman b. Affan </div>", "<div style=\"font-family:Cambria;font-size:17px;\">Caliph Mu'awiyah b. Abi Sufyan </div>", "<div style=\"font-family:Cambria;font-size:17px;\">Caliph Umar b. Abdul-Aziz  <br/> </div>"], "answer": 3, "explanation": "<div style=\"font-family:Cambria;font-size:17px;\">:\"Umar bin Abdul-Azeez was the one who facilitated the compilation of the Hadith. He was a Umayyad caliph who gave an order to the scholars to collect and compile the traditions.Umar ibn Abd al-Aziz ( Arabic : ﻋﻤﺮ ﺑﻦ ﻋﺒﺪ ﺍﻟﻌﺰﻳﺰ , romanized : ʿUmar ibn ʿAbd al-ʿAzīz ; 2 November 682 - c. 5 February 720), commonly known as Umar II ( ﻋﻤﺮ ﺍﻟﺜﺎﻧﻲ ), was the eighth Umayyad caliph , ruling from 22 September 717 until his death in 720. Umar made various significant contributions and reforms to the society, and he has been described as \"the most pious and devout\" of the Umayyad rulers and was often called the first Mujaddid and the fifth righteous Caliph of Islam.Surrounded with great scholars, he is credited with having ordered the first official collection of <br/> Hadiths and encouraged education to everyone. He also sent out emissaries to China and Tibet , inviting their rulers to accept Islam.  <br/> </div>", "topic": "HADITH : HISTORY OF HADITH LITERATURE -COLLECTION OF HADITH FROM THE TIME OF THE PROPHET-SAW TO THE PERIOD OF THE SIX AUTHENTIC COLLECTORS OF HADITH"}, {"id": "objective>IRK>2017 Model>5", "question": "<div style=\"font-family:Cambria;font-size:17px;\">The science of Asma al-rijal is introduced in order to  <br/> </div>", "options": ["<div style=\"font-family:Cambria;font-size:17px;\">Authenticate the chains of Hadith narrators </div>", "<div style=\"font-family:Cambria;font-size:17px;\">Confirms the names of Hadith books </div>", "<div style=\"font-family:Cambria;font-size:17px;\">Ascertain the number of a hadith </div>", "<div style=\"font-family:Cambria;font-size:17px;\">Explain the contents of the sunnah  <br/> </div>"], "answer": 0, "explanation": "<div style=\"font-family:Cambria;font-size:17px;\">This refers to study of men and women who transmitted hadith reports. This discipline was necessary to develop as an aid to another Hadith discipline called Al-Jarh wa al-Ta`dil . <br/> </div>", "topic": "HADITH : AUTHENTICATION OF HADITH"}, {"id": "objective>IRK>2017 Model>6", "question": "<div style=\"font-family:Cambria;font-size:17px;\">The real name of Imam al-Bukhari is  <br/> </div>", "options": ["<div style=\"font-family:Cambria;font-size:17px;\">Musa b. Muhammad </div>", "<div style=\"font-family:Cambria;font-size:17px;\">Muhammad b. Ahmad </div>", "<div style=\"font-family:Cambria;font-size:17px;\"> Isma'il b. Yaqub </div>", "<div style=\"font-family:Cambria;font-size:17px;\">Muhammad b. Isma'il </div>"], "answer": 3, "explanation": "<div style=\"font-family:Cambria;font-size:17px;\">His full name was Muhammad ibn Ismail ibn Ibrahim ibn al-Mughirah ibn Bardizbah al-Bukhari. He was an scholar and teacher, he had a good knowledge about Tirmidhi. <br/> </div>", "topic": "HADITH : HISTORY OF HADITH LITERATURE -COLLECTION OF HADITH FROM THE TIME OF THE PROPHET-SAW TO THE PERIOD OF THE SIX AUTHENTIC COLLECTORS OF HADITH"}, {"id": "objective>IRK>2017 Model>7", "question": "<div style=\"font-family:Cambria;font-size:17px;\">A Hadith in which the chain of narration and text are sound is known as  <br/> </div>", "options": ["<div style=\"font-family:Cambria;font-size:17px;\">Mash'hur </div>", "<div style=\"font-family:Cambria;font-size:17px;\">Maqtu</div>", "<div style=\"font-family:Cambria;font-size:17px;\">Mursa</div>", "<div style=\"font-family:Cambria;font-size:17px;\">Sahih </div>"], "answer": 3, "explanation": "<div style=\"font-family:Cambria;font-size:17px;\">Ḥadīth is the Arabic word for things like speech, report, account, narrative. ... Individual hadith are classified by Muslim clerics and jurists into categories such as <br/> sahih (\"authentic\"), hasan (\"good\") or da'if (\"weak\"). However, different groups and different scholars may classify a <br/> hadith differently. <br/> </div>", "topic": "HADITH : AUTHENTICATION OF HADITH"}, {"id": "objective>IRK>2017 Model>8", "question": "<div style=\"font-family:Cambria;font-size:17px;\">Which of the following directly applies to Hadith ad-Da'if?  <br/> </div>", "options": ["<div style=\"font-family:Cambria;font-size:17px;\">It can be used on certain conditions </div>", "<div style=\"font-family:Cambria;font-size:17px;\">Its rejection is due to its weakness all the times </div>", "<div style=\"font-family:Cambria;font-size:17px;\">It can be equated with al- Mauduf </div>", "<div style=\"font-family:Cambria;font-size:17px;\">It's legal status cannot be ascertained </div>"], "answer": 0, "explanation": "<div style=\"font-family:Cambria;font-size:17px;\">A da'if hadith is a hadith which does not fulfil the conditions of the sahih or hassan hadith. Hadith A da'if is considered weak, so it is mostly not used, but it can be used on certain conditions, if found useful.  <br/> </div>", "topic": "HADITH : AUTHENTICATION OF HADITH"}, {"id": "objective>IRK>2017 Model>9", "question": "<div style=\"font-family:Cambria;font-size:17px;\">The Glorious Qur'ǻn takes precedence over the Hadith in that  <br/> </div>", "options": ["<div style=\"font-family:Cambria;font-size:17px;\">it can be used for prayers </div>", "<div style=\"font-family:Cambria;font-size:17px;\">the former is recited in prayers </div>", "<div style=\"font-family:Cambria;font-size:17px;\">the latter can be invoked against evil </div>", "<div style=\"font-family:Cambria;font-size:17px;\">only the former is used in judicial matters  <br/> </div>"], "answer": 2, "explanation": "<div style=\"font-family:Cambria;font-size:17px;\">Qu'ran is received during salat, Hadith is not to be used during salat. <br/> Qur'an and Hadith are two vital sources of the Islamic legislation. However, Qur'an is considered more important to the Hadith because of the following reasons: Qur'an is a word of the Creator; Allah (SWT) while Hadith is a saying of a man (such as the Prophet (s.a.w.a) or the Imams (AS)). <br/> </div>", "topic": "HADITH : THE RELATIONSHIP BETWEEN HADITH AND THE GLORIOUS QUR’AN"}, {"id": "objective>IRK>2017 Model>10", "question": "<div style=\"font-family:Cambria;font-size:17px;\">Hadith is important to Muslims because it is</div>", "options": ["<div style=\"font-family:Cambria;font-size:17px;\"> miracle of Islam </div>", "<div style=\"font-family:Cambria;font-size:17px;\">the most reliable sayings of the prophet (SAW) </div>", "<div style=\"font-family:Cambria;font-size:17px;\">the only linkage between the prophet (SAW) and the Muslim </div>", "<div style=\"font-family:Cambria;font-size:17px;\">the means through which the prophet's message is known  <br/> </div>"], "answer": 3, "explanation": "<div style=\"font-family:Cambria;font-size:17px;\">Hadith, Arabic Ḥadīth (\"News\" or \"Story\"), also spelled Hadīt, record of the traditions or sayings of the Prophet Muhammad, revered and received as a major source of religious law and moral guidance, second only to the authority of the Qurʾān, the holy book of Islam. Muslims read and study Hadith to be able to live a holy life that pleases Allah following the lessons container in the Hadith. <br/> </div>", "topic": "HADITH : THE RELATIONSHIP BETWEEN HADITH AND THE GLORIOUS QUR’AN"}, {"id": "objective>IRK>2017 Model>11", "question": "<div style=\"font-family:Cambria;font-size:17px;\">The type of Zakah due at the end of Ramadan fast is known as  <br/> </div>", "options": ["<div style=\"font-family:Cambria;font-size:17px;\">Zakah al-mal </div>", "<div style=\"font-family:Cambria;font-size:17px;\">Zakah al-fitr </div>", "<div style=\"font-family:Cambria;font-size:17px;\">Zakah al-anam </div>", "<div style=\"font-family:Cambria;font-size:17px;\">Zakah al-harth </div>"], "answer": 1, "explanation": "<div style=\"font-family:Cambria;font-size:17px;\">Zakat al-Fitr is a charity taken for the poor a few days before the end of fasting in the Islamic holy month of Ramadan. The Arabic word Fitr means the same as iftar, breaking a fast, and it comes from the same root word as Futoor which means breakfast.  <br/> </div>", "topic": "IBADAT AND THEIR TYPES : ZAKAH"}, {"id": "objective>IRK>2017 Model>12", "question": "<div style=\"font-family:Cambria;font-size:17px;\">The gathering of pilgrims on the 9th day of Dhul Hijjah is known as</div>", "options": ["<div style=\"font-family:Cambria;font-size:17px;\">Wuquf bi 'Arefah </div>", "<div style=\"font-family:Cambria;font-size:17px;\">Sajadah 'Arefah </div>", "<div style=\"font-family:Cambria;font-size:17px;\">Jabal 'Arefah </div>", "<div style=\"font-family:Cambria;font-size:17px;\">Da'al al- 'Arefah  <br/> </div>"], "answer": 0, "explanation": "<div style=\"font-family:Cambria;font-size:17px;\">The Day of Arafat falls on the second day of pilgrimage rituals. At dawn on this day, nearly 2 million Muslim pilgrims will make their way from the town of Mina to a nearby hillside and plain called Mount Arafat and the Plain of Arafat, which is located about 12.5 miles (20 kilometers) from Mecca, the final destination for the pilgrimage.  <br/> Every Muslim is expected to make the pilgrimage to once during his or her lifetime. During the afternoon, from about noon until sunset, Muslim pilgrims stand in earnest supplication and devotion, praying for God's abundant forgiveness, and listening to Islamic scholars speak on issues of religious and moral importance. Tears are shed readily as those who gather make repentance and seek God's mercy, recite words of prayer and remembrance and gather together as equals before their Lord. The day closes upon the recitation of the evening prayer of Al-Maghrib. <br/> For many Muslims, the Day of Arafat proves to be the most memorable part of the hajj pilgrimage, and one that stays with them forever. <br/> </div>", "topic": "IBADAT AND THEIR TYPES : HAJJ"}, {"id": "objective>IRK>2017 Model>13", "question": "<div style=\"font-family:Cambria;font-size:17px;\">The categories of women prohibited in marriage due to blood relations are  <br/> </div>", "options": ["<div style=\"font-family:Cambria;font-size:17px;\">14</div>", "<div style=\"font-family:Cambria;font-size:17px;\">11</div>", "<div style=\"font-family:Cambria;font-size:17px;\">10</div>", "<div style=\"font-family:Cambria;font-size:17px;\">73</div>"], "answer": 2, "explanation": "<div style=\"font-family:Cambria;font-size:17px;\">The categories of women prohibited in marriage due to blood relation is '10' according to the Qu'ran. <br/> </div>", "topic": "FAMILY MATTERS : MARRIAGE"}, {"id": "objective>IRK>2017 Model>14", "question": "<div style=\"font-family:Cambria;font-size:17px;\">According to Q.4:34, the main right of the husband over his wife is to  <br/> </div>", "options": ["<div style=\"font-family:Cambria;font-size:17px;\">Prepare food for him </div>", "<div style=\"font-family:Cambria;font-size:17px;\">Have conjugal relation with her </div>", "<div style=\"font-family:Cambria;font-size:17px;\">Accept his leadership and obey him </div>", "<div style=\"font-family:Cambria;font-size:17px;\">Appreciate him for his favours </div>"], "answer": 2, "explanation": "<div style=\"font-family:Cambria;font-size:17px;\">So good women are the obedient, guarding in secret that which Allah hath guarded. As for those from whom ye fear rebellion, admonish them and banish them to beds apart, and scourge them. Then if they obey you, seek not a way against them.</div>", "topic": "FAMILY MATTERS : MARRIAGE"}, {"id": "objective>IRK>2017 Model>15", "question": "<div style=\"font-family:Cambria;font-size:17px;\">A marriage is not valid in Islam without  <br/> </div>", "options": ["<div style=\"font-family:Cambria;font-size:17px;\">At least two witnesses </div>", "<div style=\"font-family:Cambria;font-size:17px;\">Slaughtering an animal </div>", "<div style=\"font-family:Cambria;font-size:17px;\">Marriage garment </div>", "<div style=\"font-family:Cambria;font-size:17px;\">Deciding the place of residence </div>"], "answer": 0, "explanation": "<div style=\"font-family:Cambria;font-size:17px;\">: In Islam according to the Qu'ran for a marriage to be valid there must be at least two witness present, one from each side and they must reach a mutual agreement, for the marriage to be valid and blessed.  \"For validity of marriage, there must be at least two witnesses\" <br/> </div>", "topic": "FAMILY MATTERS : MARRIAGE"}, {"id": "objective>IRK>2017 Model>16", "question": "<div style=\"font-family:Cambria;font-size:17px;\">Which of the following is the correct order of authenticity of three of the six sound collections of the Hadith  <br/> </div>", "options": ["<div style=\"font-family:Cambria;font-size:17px;\">Bukhari, Muslim and Tirmidhi </div>", "<div style=\"font-family:Cambria;font-size:17px;\">Ibn Majah, Muslim and Nasa'i </div>", "<div style=\"font-family:Cambria;font-size:17px;\">Muslim, Nasa'I and Ibn Majah </div>", "<div style=\"font-family:Cambria;font-size:17px;\">Abu Dawud, Tirmidhi and Bukhari </div>"], "answer": 0, "explanation": "<div style=\"font-family:Cambria;font-size:17px;\">'Bukhari, Muslim and Tirmidhi' they are part of the six compilers and collectors of the Hadith. They were great scholars and teachers of the Hadith, filled with great knowledge of the Hadith.</div>", "topic": "HADITH : THE STUDY OF THE ARABIC TEXTS OF THE FOLLOWING AHADITH FROMAN-NAWAWI’S COLLECTION: 1,3,5,6,7,9,10,11,12,13,15,16, 18,19,21,22,25,27,34, AND 41"}, {"id": "objective>IRK>2017 Model>17", "question": "<div style=\"font-family:Cambria;font-size:17px;\">The first major written work of a hadith was  <br/> </div>", "options": ["<div style=\"font-family:Cambria;font-size:17px;\">Sahih Muslim </div>", "<div style=\"font-family:Cambria;font-size:17px;\">Sunan Ibn Majah </div>", "<div style=\"font-family:Cambria;font-size:17px;\">Muwata Malik </div>", "<div style=\"font-family:Cambria;font-size:17px;\">Musnad Ahmad </div>"], "answer": 2, "explanation": "<div style=\"font-family:Cambria;font-size:17px;\">:\"The Muwatta of Imam Malik bin Annab (died 179AH) is the first of its kind ..  <br/> Muwatta Imam Malik. The Muwaṭṭaʾ (Arabic: ﺍﻟﻤﻮﻃﺄ , \"well-trodden path\") or Muwatta Imam Malik ‏( :Arabic ﻣﻮﻃﺄ ﺍﻹﻣﺎﻡ ﻣﺎﻟﻚ ) of Imam Malik (711-795) written in the 8th-century, is the earliest collection of hadith texts comprising the subjects of Islamic law, compiled by the Imam , Malik ibn Anas. <br/> </div>", "topic": "HADITH : HISTORY OF HADITH LITERATURE -COLLECTION OF HADITH FROM THE TIME OF THE PROPHET-SAW TO THE PERIOD OF THE SIX AUTHENTIC COLLECTORS OF HADITH"}, {"id": "objective>IRK>2017 Model>18", "question": "<div style=\"font-family:Cambria;font-size:17px;\">The collection of Imam Muslim differs from that of Imam Bukhari in terms of  <br/> </div>", "options": ["<div style=\"font-family:Cambria;font-size:17px;\"> Interpretation </div>", "<div style=\"font-family:Cambria;font-size:17px;\">Authenticity</div>", "<div style=\"font-family:Cambria;font-size:17px;\">Repetition</div>", "<div style=\"font-family:Cambria;font-size:17px;\">Clasification</div>"], "answer": 3, "explanation": "<div style=\"font-family:Cambria;font-size:17px;\">: Imam Muslim strictly observed many principles of the science of Hadith, which had been slightly ignored by his great teacher Imam Bukhari (may Allah have mercy on both of them). Imam Muslims classified his writing genuinely and overlooked any writing that it account didn't match thoroughly. <br/> </div>", "topic": "HADITH : THE SIX SOUND COLLECTORS OF HADITH – BIOGRAPHIES AND THEIR WORKS."}, {"id": "objective>IRK>2017 Model>19", "question": "<div style=\"font-family:Cambria;font-size:17px;\">Hadith 11 of an-Nawawi admonishes Muslims to </div>", "options": ["<div style=\"font-family:Cambria;font-size:17px;\">be certain in some acts of worship </div>", "<div style=\"font-family:Cambria;font-size:17px;\">avoid doubtful things </div>", "<div style=\"font-family:Cambria;font-size:17px;\">note that doubt and uncertainty are close to each other </div>", "<div style=\"font-family:Cambria;font-size:17px;\">always do things clearly </div>"], "answer": 1, "explanation": "<div style=\"font-family:Cambria;font-size:17px;\">\"...Leave that about which you are in doubt for that about which you are in no doubt\"  <br/> Al-Hasan bin Ali who said: I committed to memory from the Messenger of Allah, sallallahu alayhi wasallam, (the following words): \"Leave that about which you are in doubt for that about which you are in no doubt.\" [Al-Tirmidhi and al-Nasaii related it, and al-Tirmidhi said: It is a good and genuine Hadith]. Truth will lead to tranquility and falsehood will lead to doubt. We must all act and do what is permissible and proper. <br/> </div>", "topic": "HADITH : THE STUDY OF THE ARABIC TEXTS OF THE FOLLOWING AHADITH FROMAN-NAWAWI’S COLLECTION: 1,3,5,6,7,9,10,11,12,13,15,16, 18,19,21,22,25,27,34, AND 41"}, {"id": "objective>IRK>2017 Model>20", "question": "<div style=\"font-family:Cambria;font-size:17px;\">According to Hadith 41 of an- Nawawi, the faith of a believer is incomplete until he  <br/> </div>", "options": ["<div style=\"font-family:Cambria;font-size:17px;\">Loves for his brother what he love himself </div>", "<div style=\"font-family:Cambria;font-size:17px;\">Hate all kinds of evil </div>", "<div style=\"font-family:Cambria;font-size:17px;\">Likes good things for his family </div>", "<div style=\"font-family:Cambria;font-size:17px;\"> Follows what has been revealed unto the prophet(SAW) </div>"], "answer": 3, "explanation": "<div style=\"font-family:Cambria;font-size:17px;\">\"None of you (truly) believes until his desire or inclination is in accordance with what I have brought or subservient to what I came with.\" <br/> \"We should love the Prophet (SAWS) wholeheartedly. So, your wishes would be in accordance with the noble sunnah. Your tendencies would always be towards the Prophet's (SAWS) orders. This is ikhlas\"sincerity\".This hadith has been interpreted this to mean that \"a person is not a Muslim unless he accepts what is in the Qur'aan and Sunnah without grudge and resistance. \"But no, by your Lord, they can have no Faith [Eemaan] until they make you (O Muhammad, Sallallaahu `alayhi wa sallam) judge in all disputes between them, and find in themselves no resistance against your decisions, and accept (them) with full submission\"  <br/> </div>", "topic": "HADITH : THE STUDY OF THE ARABIC TEXTS OF THE FOLLOWING AHADITH FROMAN-NAWAWI’S COLLECTION: 1,3,5,6,7,9,10,11,12,13,15,16, 18,19,21,22,25,27,34, AND 41"}, {"id": "objective>IRK>2017 Model>21", "question": "<div style=\"font-family:Cambria;font-size:17px;\">The important of Salah as listed in Q. 29:45 includes  <br/> </div>", "options": ["<div style=\"font-family:Cambria;font-size:17px;\"> Prohibition of shameful and deeds </div>", "<div style=\"font-family:Cambria;font-size:17px;\"> Making invocations regularly </div>", "<div style=\"font-family:Cambria;font-size:17px;\">Prohibition of cheating in measures </div>", "<div style=\"font-family:Cambria;font-size:17px;\">Prohibition of hoarding </div>"], "answer": 0, "explanation": "<div style=\"font-family:Cambria;font-size:17px;\">\"...Verily, As Salat prevent from al- Fahshai (i.e. great sins...) and Almunkar ... (every kind of evil wicked deed). Q. 29:45.  Reciting the Salah helps Muslims in preventing them from committing great sins. Plus keeping them from evil wicked deeds. <br/> </div>", "topic": "IBADAT AND THEIR TYPES : SALAH"}, {"id": "objective>IRK>2017 Model>22", "question": "<div style=\"font-family:Cambria;font-size:17px;\">Which of the following vitiates Salah?</div>", "options": ["<div style=\"font-family:Cambria;font-size:17px;\"> Intoxication </div>", "<div style=\"font-family:Cambria;font-size:17px;\">Adornment</div>", "<div style=\"font-family:Cambria;font-size:17px;\">Falsehood</div>", "<div style=\"font-family:Cambria;font-size:17px;\">yawning</div>"], "answer": 0, "explanation": "<div style=\"font-family:Cambria;font-size:17px;\">According to Sahih Muslim you shouldn't do following things while praying: <br/> a.. Clothes having designs and markings on them are distracting and should be avoided ( refer Sahih Muslim book 4, hadith 1131-1133 ) <br/> b. The Prophet commanded the believer that while praying 'he should not spit in front of him, for Allah is in front of him when he is engaged in prayer' ( refer Sahih Muslim book 4 , hadith 1116 ). According to another tradition, he 'forbade spitting on the right side or in front, but it is permissible to spit on the left side or under the left foot' ( refer Sahih Muslim book 4 , hadith 1118 ). <br/> c. To eat onion or garlic is not harm (forbidden), but Muhammad found their odors 'repugnant' (refer Sahih Muslim book 4 , hadith 1149) and therefore forbade coming to the mosque after eating them, 'for the angels are harmed by the same things as men' ( refer Sahih Muslim book 4 , hadith1145 ) . <br/> </div>", "topic": "IBADAT AND THEIR TYPES : SALAH"}, {"id": "objective>IRK>2017 Model>23", "question": "<div style=\"font-family:Cambria;font-size:17px;\">A major activity in Salah performed through various bodily postures is known as  <br/> </div>", "options": ["<div style=\"font-family:Cambria;font-size:17px;\">Raka'at </div>", "<div style=\"font-family:Cambria;font-size:17px;\">Takbiratul Ihram </div>", "<div style=\"font-family:Cambria;font-size:17px;\">At- tashahud </div>", "<div style=\"font-family:Cambria;font-size:17px;\">Sujud ash-shukr </div>"], "answer": 0, "explanation": "<div style=\"font-family:Cambria;font-size:17px;\">Raka'at \"The various bodily postures performed in Salah as a major activity is called Rakat\".   A rakat, or rakʿah, consists of the prescribed movements and words followed by Muslims while offering prayers to Allah. It also refers to a single unit of Islamic prayers.  <br/> </div>", "topic": "IBADAT AND THEIR TYPES : SALAH"}, {"id": "objective>IRK>2017 Model>24", "question": "<div style=\"font-family:Cambria;font-size:17px;\">In congregational Salah, a person who comes late is expected to  <br/> </div>", "options": ["<div style=\"font-family:Cambria;font-size:17px;\">pronounce the taslim to indicate his arrival </div>", "<div style=\"font-family:Cambria;font-size:17px;\">say subhanallah so that the Imam can note his presence </div>", "<div style=\"font-family:Cambria;font-size:17px;\">recite the iqama before joining the congregation D. make takbiratul ihram and join the Imam </div>", "<div style=\"font-family:Cambria;font-size:17px;\">make takbiratul ihram and join the Imam </div>"], "answer": 3, "explanation": "<div style=\"font-family:Cambria;font-size:17px;\">The person who joins the congregational prayer after the Imam has done a Rakah or more should first say the opening Takbir Takbirat Al Ihram while standing and then should move, directly to perform the act that the Imam is performing and when the Imam finishes the prayer he (the person who joined the prayer late) should complete what he has missed.  <br/> </div>", "topic": "IBADAT AND THEIR TYPES : SALAH"}, {"id": "objective>IRK>2017 Model>25", "question": "<div style=\"font-family:Cambria;font-size:17px;\">Hajj is one of the avenues for Islamic brotherhood and  <br/> </div>", "options": ["<div style=\"font-family:Cambria;font-size:17px;\">kindness </div>", "<div style=\"font-family:Cambria;font-size:17px;\">Fairness </div>", "<div style=\"font-family:Cambria;font-size:17px;\">Trust</div>", "<div style=\"font-family:Cambria;font-size:17px;\">Unity </div>"], "answer": 3, "explanation": "<div style=\"font-family:Cambria;font-size:17px;\">\"The Society of the Muslim Brothers ( Arabic : <br/> ﺟﻤﺎﻋﺔ ﺍﻹﺧﻮﺍﻥ ﺍﻟﻤﺴﻠﻤﻴﻦ Jamāʿat al-Ikhwān al-Muslimīn ) , better known as the Muslim Brotherhood\" it was founded in 1928. Motto: Islam is the solution. <br/> </div>", "topic": "IBADAT AND THEIR TYPES : HAJJ"}, {"id": "objective>IRK>2017 Model>26", "question": "<div style=\"font-family:Cambria;font-size:17px;\">The message in Hadith 34 of an- Nawawi is about  <br/> </div>", "options": ["<div style=\"font-family:Cambria;font-size:17px;\"> Performing the society for the better </div>", "<div style=\"font-family:Cambria;font-size:17px;\">Preventing evil in the society by any means possible </div>", "<div style=\"font-family:Cambria;font-size:17px;\">Commanding good among people </div>", "<div style=\"font-family:Cambria;font-size:17px;\">Abstaining from evil deeds </div>"], "answer": 1, "explanation": "<div style=\"font-family:Cambria;font-size:17px;\">:  .....\"\"Whosoever of you sees an evil, let him change it with his hand; and if he is not able to do so, then [let him change it] with his tongue; and if he is not able to do so, then with his heart - and that is the weakest of faith.\" The message here is that we should encourage doing good, and doing everything in our power in rebuking bad things. <br/> </div>", "topic": "MORAL LESSONS IN THE GLORIOUS QUR'AN AND HADITH : ENJOINING WHAT IS GOOD AND FORBIDDING WHAT IS WRONG HADITH 25 AND 34 OF AN NAWAWI"}, {"id": "objective>IRK>2017 Model>27", "question": "<div style=\"font-family:Cambria;font-size:17px;\"><img src=\"data:image/png;base64,\" style=\"position:relative;max-width:100%;\"/> <br/> The Hadith above warns Muslims against charity with  <br/> </div>", "options": ["<div style=\"font-family:Cambria;font-size:17px;\">useless things </div>", "<div style=\"font-family:Cambria;font-size:17px;\"> ill-gotten wealth </div>", "<div style=\"font-family:Cambria;font-size:17px;\">evil intention </div>", "<div style=\"font-family:Cambria;font-size:17px;\">cheap things  <br/> </div>"], "answer": 1, "explanation": "<div style=\"font-family:Cambria;font-size:17px;\">\"...Allah the Mighty is good and accepts only that which is good...\"  <br/> This is the best way in giving charity; Volunteer in a shelter or NGO <br/> - Visit an elderly or sick person. ... <br/> - Sign up to an aid project. ... <br/> -Teach. <br/> -Remembrance (dhikr) of Allah. <br/> </div>", "topic": "HADITH : THE STUDY OF THE ARABIC TEXTS OF THE FOLLOWING AHADITH FROMAN-NAWAWI’S COLLECTION: 1,3,5,6,7,9,10,11,12,13,15,16, 18,19,21,22,25,27,34, AND 41"}, {"id": "objective>IRK>2017 Model>28", "question": "<div style=\"font-family:Cambria;font-size:17px;\">Q. 3:103 enjoins Muslims to  <br/> </div>", "options": ["<div style=\"font-family:Cambria;font-size:17px;\">Unite and not be divided </div>", "<div style=\"font-family:Cambria;font-size:17px;\">Live in the same place </div>", "<div style=\"font-family:Cambria;font-size:17px;\">Speak with one voice politically </div>", "<div style=\"font-family:Cambria;font-size:17px;\"> Unite for economic progress </div>"], "answer": 0, "explanation": "<div style=\"font-family:Cambria;font-size:17px;\">Q.3:103 \"Hold fast together to the cable of Allah, and be not divided. Remember the blessing that Allah bestowed upon you: you were once enemies then He brought your hearts together, so that through His blessing you became brothers. You stood on the brink of a pit of fire and He delivered you from it.  Thus Allah makes His signs clear to you that you may be guided to the right way.\" The message here enjoins us to be United and surpport each other. <br/> </div>", "topic": "MORAL LESSONS IN THE GLORIOUS QUR'AN AND HADITH : UNITY AND BROTHERHOOD HADITH 35 OF AN-NAWAWI"}, {"id": "objective>IRK>2017 Model>29", "question": "<div style=\"font-family:Cambria;font-size:17px;\">Good behavior and modesty in dress in Islam is an essential parts of  <br/> </div>", "options": ["<div style=\"font-family:Cambria;font-size:17px;\">Amal</div>", "<div style=\"font-family:Cambria;font-size:17px;\">Duty</div>", "<div style=\"font-family:Cambria;font-size:17px;\">Iman </div>", "<div style=\"font-family:Cambria;font-size:17px;\">beauty</div>"], "answer": 0, "explanation": "<div style=\"font-family:Cambria;font-size:17px;\">Amal means any action or deed. It can be good or bad. As per Islam the reward or punishment of amal is based on neeyah (intention). ... In Islam, first priority should be given to diplomacy and dialogue. <br/> </div>", "topic": "MORAL LESSONS IN THE GLORIOUS QUR'AN AND HADITH : BEHAVIOUR AND MODESTY IN DRESSING"}, {"id": "objective>IRK>2017 Model>30", "question": "<div style=\"font-family:Cambria;font-size:17px;\">Hadith 18 of an-Nwawai enjoins believers to  <br/> </div>", "options": ["<div style=\"font-family:Cambria;font-size:17px;\">Be firm abravend </div>", "<div style=\"font-family:Cambria;font-size:17px;\">Be strong-minded and clean </div>", "<div style=\"font-family:Cambria;font-size:17px;\">Have piety and work righteously </div>", "<div style=\"font-family:Cambria;font-size:17px;\">Acquire knowledge and be polite  <br/> </div>"], "answer": 2, "explanation": "<div style=\"font-family:Cambria;font-size:17px;\">On the authority of Abu Dharr, Jundub ibn Junadah, and Abu Abdul Rahman Mu'adh ibn jabal (May Allah be pleased with both of them) from the Messenger of Allah (peace and blessings of Allah be upon him) who said: \"Fear Allah wherever you are. And follow up a bad deed with a good deed and it will wipe it out. And behave towards the people with good behaviour\". <br/> </div>", "topic": "MORAL LESSONS IN THE GLORIOUS QUR'AN AND HADITH : PIETY-TAQWA HADITH 18 AND 35 OF AN NAWAWI"}, {"id": "objective>IRK>2017 Model>31", "question": "<div style=\"font-family:Cambria;font-size:17px;\">Prophet Muhammad (SAW) was described as the seal of all prophets, meaning that he  <br/> </div>", "options": ["<div style=\"font-family:Cambria;font-size:17px;\">Was the last or the prophets of Allah </div>", "<div style=\"font-family:Cambria;font-size:17px;\">Covered all parts of the world preaching </div>", "<div style=\"font-family:Cambria;font-size:17px;\">Is reserved even by the Jews </div>", "<div style=\"font-family:Cambria;font-size:17px;\">Was accepted by all Christian  <br/> </div>"], "answer": 0, "explanation": "<div style=\"font-family:Cambria;font-size:17px;\">\"Muhammad is not the father of any of your men, but (he is) the Messenger of Allah, and the Seal of the Prophets: and Allah has full knowledge of all things.\" <br/> - The Qur'an - Chapter 33 Verse 40 <br/> </div>", "topic": "THE LIFE OF PROPHET MUHAMMAD (SAW) : HIS CALL TO PROPHETHOOD"}, {"id": "objective>IRK>2017 Model>32", "question": "<div style=\"font-family:Cambria;font-size:17px;\">The act of taking refuge from the Jinns as mentioned in Q. 72:6 is that  <br/> </div>", "options": ["<div style=\"font-family:Cambria;font-size:17px;\">They could harm the believers </div>", "<div style=\"font-family:Cambria;font-size:17px;\">People benefit from their protection </div>", "<div style=\"font-family:Cambria;font-size:17px;\">They would increase such people in fury </div>", "<div style=\"font-family:Cambria;font-size:17px;\">people may turn to be their partners <br/> </div>"], "answer": 2, "explanation": "<div style=\"font-family:Cambria;font-size:17px;\">\"And verily there were men going mankind who took shelter with the males among the Jin but the (the Jin) increase them (the mankind) in sin and transgression\". Q. 72:6. <br/> </div>", "topic": "ARTICLE OF FAITH : BELIEF IN ALLAH'S ANGELS"}, {"id": "objective>IRK>2017 Model>33", "question": "<div style=\"font-family:Cambria;font-size:17px;\">The attributes of Allah as contained in Q.59:23 are  <br/> </div>", "options": ["<div style=\"font-family:Cambria;font-size:17px;\">5</div>", "<div style=\"font-family:Cambria;font-size:17px;\">6</div>", "<div style=\"font-family:Cambria;font-size:17px;\">7</div>", "<div style=\"font-family:Cambria;font-size:17px;\">8</div>"], "answer": 3, "explanation": "<div style=\"font-family:Cambria;font-size:17px;\">\"The attributes of Allah as contained in Q59: 23 are 8. i.e. 1. The king 2. The Holy 3. The one free from all defects 4. The Giver of security 5. The watcher over his creator 6. The Al-Mighty 7. The compeller 8. The supreme.</div>", "topic": "ARTICLE OF FAITH : BELIEF IN ALLAH"}, {"id": "objective>IRK>2017 Model>34", "question": "<div style=\"font-family:Cambria;font-size:17px;\">34.′Lā yukallifu Hāhu naf san illā wus'ahā' This quotation is part of  <br/> </div>", "options": ["<div style=\"font-family:Cambria;font-size:17px;\">Sūrat al - Alaq </div>", "<div style=\"font-family:Cambria;font-size:17px;\">Sūrat al - A 'lā </div>", "<div style=\"font-family:Cambria;font-size:17px;\">Ayāt al - kur'ay </div>", "<div style=\"font-family:Cambria;font-size:17px;\">Ayāt Amanar - Rasūl</div>"], "answer": 3, "explanation": "<div style=\"font-family:Cambria;font-size:17px;\">Surah. 2:285:6 \"In the Name of Allah, the Beneficent, the Merciful. <br/> The Apostle, and the believers with him, <br/> believe in what has been bestowed upon him from on high <br/> by his Sustainer: they all believe in God, and His angels, <br/> and His revelations, and His apostles, <br/> making no distinction between any of His apostles; and they say: <br/> \"We have heard, and we pay heed. Grant us Thy forgiveness, O our Sustainer, <br/> for with Thee is all journeys' end! <br/> \"God does not burden any human being with more than he is well able to bear...\" <br/> </div>", "topic": "STUDY OF THE ARABIC TEXT OF THE FOLLOWING SUWAR/AYATS WITH TAJWID : AMANAR-RASUL"}, {"id": "objective>IRK>2017 Model>35", "question": "<div style=\"font-family:Cambria;font-size:17px;\">'Surely, we created man of the best stature, then, we reduced him to the lowest of the low save those who believe and good works' This quotation is from Surat  <br/> </div>", "options": ["<div style=\"font-family:Cambria;font-size:17px;\">al Asr </div>", "<div style=\"font-family:Cambria;font-size:17px;\"> al-Alaq </div>", "<div style=\"font-family:Cambria;font-size:17px;\">al-Tīn </div>", "<div style=\"font-family:Cambria;font-size:17px;\">al-Bayyinah </div>"], "answer": 2, "explanation": "<div style=\"font-family:Cambria;font-size:17px;\">The quotation 'Surely, we created man of the best stature, then, we reduced him to the lowest of the low save those who believe and good works' is from Surat al-Tīn. Surat al-Tīn is the 95th sura of the Quran with 8 verses.</div>", "topic": "STUDY OF THE ARABIC TEXT OF THE FOLLOWING SUWAR/AYATS WITH TAJWID : AT-TIN"}, {"id": "objective>IRK>2017 Model>36", "question": "<div style=\"font-family:Cambria;font-size:17px;\">The memorization, recording and compilation of the Qur'ān ensured its  <br/> </div>", "options": ["<div style=\"font-family:Cambria;font-size:17px;\">divine nature </div>", "<div style=\"font-family:Cambria;font-size:17px;\">divine authority </div>", "<div style=\"font-family:Cambria;font-size:17px;\">Authenticity</div>", "<div style=\"font-family:Cambria;font-size:17px;\">eternity</div>"], "answer": 2, "explanation": "<div style=\"font-family:Cambria;font-size:17px;\">Memorizing and recording the Quran, so that it can be the same in the future and there will not be any conflicting words, statement or teaching in the Quran shows it's authenticity and it's originality. <br/> </div>", "topic": "PRESERVATION OF THE GLORIOUS QUR’AN : RECORDING, COMPILATION AND STANDARDIZATION OF THE GLORIOUS QUR’AN"}, {"id": "objective>IRK>2017 Model>37", "question": "<div style=\"font-family:Cambria;font-size:17px;\"> <img src=\"data:image/png;base64,\" style=\"position:relative;max-width:100%;\"/> <br/> 'Inna mā yurīdu ash-shaytānu an yūqi 'abaynakumul adāwata wal-baghdā fil khamr wal-maysir (Q. 5:91) The verse quoted above enumerates the evils of  <br/> </div>", "options": ["<div style=\"font-family:Cambria;font-size:17px;\">wine and adultery </div>", "<div style=\"font-family:Cambria;font-size:17px;\">gambling an adultery </div>", "<div style=\"font-family:Cambria;font-size:17px;\">adultery and divining arrows </div>", "<div style=\"font-family:Cambria;font-size:17px;\">wine and gambling </div>"], "answer": 3, "explanation": "<div style=\"font-family:Cambria;font-size:17px;\">The statement educates us about the evil in drinking to stupor  and gambling with our money and time which Allah  frowns at. So we should deceit and distance ourselves from drinking to stupor and gambling. <br/> </div>", "topic": "MORAL LESSONS IN THE GLORIOUS QUR’AN AND HADITH : PROHIBITION OF BRIBERY AND CORRUPTION (Q:2:188), ALCOHOL AND GAMBLING (Q.2:219) (Q.5:93-94), STEALING AND FRAUD (Q.5:41) (83:1-5),SMOKING, DRUG ABUSE AND OTHER INTOXICANTS (Q.2:172-173, 195 AND 219) (Q.4:43) (Q.5:3) (Q.6:118-121) ARROGANCE (Q.31:18-19) AND EXTRAVAGANCE (Q.17:26-27) (Q.31:18-19)"}, {"id": "objective>IRK>2017 Model>38", "question": "<div style=\"font-family:Cambria;font-size:17px;\">One of the strong proofs of the authenticity of the Qur'ān is that  <br/> </div>", "options": ["<div style=\"font-family:Cambria;font-size:17px;\">the like of it has not been produced by an individual or a group of people </div>", "<div style=\"font-family:Cambria;font-size:17px;\">the Arabic language in which it was revealed is still spoken </div>", "<div style=\"font-family:Cambria;font-size:17px;\"> it was compiled soon after its revelation </div>", "<div style=\"font-family:Cambria;font-size:17px;\"> it has been translated into many languages </div>"], "answer": 0, "explanation": "<div style=\"font-family:Cambria;font-size:17px;\">One of the things that proves the authenticity of Islam is that no one of people have produced or bring up similar religion.</div>", "topic": "PROOF OF THE DIVINE AUTHENTICITY OF THE GLORIOUS QUR'AN : UNIQUENESS OF THE GLORIOUS QUR'AN"}, {"id": "objective>IRK>2017 Model>39", "question": "<div style=\"font-family:Cambria;font-size:17px;\">The first Islamic university established is West Africa was in  <br/> </div>", "options": ["<div style=\"font-family:Cambria;font-size:17px;\"> Aghades </div>", "<div style=\"font-family:Cambria;font-size:17px;\">Sankore</div>", "<div style=\"font-family:Cambria;font-size:17px;\">Timbuktu</div>", "<div style=\"font-family:Cambria;font-size:17px;\">Gao</div>"], "answer": 2, "explanation": "<div style=\"font-family:Cambria;font-size:17px;\">Starting out as a seasonal settlement, Timbuktu in Mali became a permanent settlement early in the 12th century. After a shift in trading routes, the town flourished from the trade in salt, gold, ivory and slaves. It became part of the Mali Empire early in the 14th century. By this time it had become a major centre of learning in the area.  <br/> </div>", "topic": "CONTRIBUTIONS OF ISLAM TO EDUCATION : ISLAMIC EDUCATION INSTITUTIONS: HOUSE OF WISDOM IN BAGHDAD, AL-AZHAR UNIVERSITY IN CAIRO AND NIZAMIYYAH UNIVERSITY IN BAGHDAD."}, {"id": "objective>IRK>2017 Model>40", "question": "<div style=\"font-family:Cambria;font-size:17px;\">The initial spread of Islam in West Africa can be described as generally  <br/> </div>", "options": ["<div style=\"font-family:Cambria;font-size:17px;\">rapid and systematic</div>", "<div style=\"font-family:Cambria;font-size:17px;\">rapid and thorough </div>", "<div style=\"font-family:Cambria;font-size:17px;\">slow but peaceful </div>", "<div style=\"font-family:Cambria;font-size:17px;\">peaceful and systematic </div>"], "answer": 3, "explanation": "<div style=\"font-family:Cambria;font-size:17px;\">The introduction of Islam to West Africa was done without violence and it was systematically done in a way that everything went perfectly well. <br/> </div>", "topic": "EARLY CONTACT OF ISLAM WITH AFRICA : THE ROLE OF TRADERS, TEACHERS, PREACHERS, MURABITUN, SUFI ORDERS AND MUJADDIDUN TO THE SPREAD OF ISLAM IN WEST AFRICA."}];
